<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN240-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. āyaik kuṭṭuvaṉkīraṉār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN240">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>āṭunaṭaip puraviyuṅ kaḷiṟun tērum</l>
<l>vāṭā yāṇar nāṭu mūrum</l>
<l>pāṭunark karukā vāa yaṇṭiraṉ</l>
<l>kōṭēn talkuṟ kuṟuntoṭi makaḷiroṭu</l>
<l>kāla ṉeṉṉuṅ kaṇṇili yuyppa</l>
<l>mēlō rulaka meytiṉa ṉeṉāap</l>
<l>potta vaṟaiyuṭ pōḻvāyk kūkai</l>
<l>cuṭṭuk kuviyeṉac cettōrp payiruṅ</l>
<l>kaḷḷiyam paṟantalai voruciṟai yalki</l>
<l>yoḷḷeri naippa vuṭampu māyantatu</l>
<l>pulleṉ kaṇṇar puravalark kāṇātu</l>
<l>kalleṉ cuṟṟamoṭu kaiyaḻintu pulavar</l>
<l>vāṭiya paciya rākippiṟar</l>
<l>nāṭupaṭu celaviṉa rāyiṉa riṉiyē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="3">“Āay Aṇṭiraṉ who was not scarce to singers </l>
<l corresp="1">with horses with prancing gait, elephants bulle, chariots, </l>
<l corresp="2">lands of unfading fertility and villages, </l>
<l corresp="5">when the eyeless man called Kālaṉ sent him </l>
<l corresp="4">along with [his] women with hips eminent in [their] curves [and] small bracelets, </l>
<l corresp="6">he reached the world of those above,” so thinking, </l>
<l corresp="9">staying on one side of the spurge waste land </l>
<l> where owls with cleft beaks call the dead: </l>
<l>“heap [them] after burning in the hollow chamber”, (7f.)</l>
<l corresp="10">[his] body vanished when the bright flames burned [it]. </l>
<l corresp="12d"> The poets, </l>
<l corresp="11"> with empty eyes, not seeing a protector </l>
<l corresp="12a-c">desolate along with [their] noisy retinue, </l>
<l corresp="13a-c">being faded from hunger </l>
<l corresp="13c-14">they now have become people who go to face the lands of others. </l>     
</lg>
    </div>
